                            <comment id="13895127" author="garydgregory" created="Fri, 7 Feb 2014 22:18:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like a bug, probably a cut and paste error. This should be fixed in 4.0 since we cannot break binary compatibility.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13895827" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sun, 9 Feb 2014 04:25:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think Exceptions are part of the method signature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AFAIK, this would only break source compatibility&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13895985" author="garydgregory" created="Sun, 9 Feb 2014 19:00:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Clirr does not complain, so it is OK to break source compatibility for 3.3?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13896119" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2014 00:25:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would say breaking source compatibility is OK, provided that this is clearly documented in the release notes.&lt;/p&gt;

